The paper deals with a cryptographic problem (Russian cards problem) and proposes a new notion of security (epsilon-strong security) for it. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of probability and communication strategies, which are common topics in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and their performance, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical proofs and analysis, which is also a common topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
